{
  "stem": "1858.3",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And I always thought of home, of my parents, of the holidays, of Passover, of Friday night, the table bedecked with all kinds of goodies and the whole family sitting around and singing.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "How happy I was.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "How I missed those days.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But how hungry I was.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And all that food on the table-- and here I was so hungry, so very hungry.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "How does one describe a hunger?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You know, I would have bitten into the machine if I could chew it.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "How do I tell you what-- how hungry I was?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Hunger was a daily problem faced by all the inmates.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But, you know, hunger is a devastating weapon.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Hunger strips you first of your strength, of your dignity, of your pride.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Hunger also strips you of your identity.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Hunger also strips you sometimes of the will to fight back and often also of your will to live, to go on.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And once you gave up, once you did not care, you perished.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There was nothing to sustain you.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But, you know, even though starvation depleted our bodies, the link among the prisoners who shared the same room provided a life-sustaining force.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And a feeling of solidarity tended to develop among the girls who shared the same room.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We would help each other.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We would give courage to each other so as to maintain some kind of order and unity in our miserable life.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "There were no stealings and there was no squealing in our camp.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
